seed | a Common Sense CMS from The Media Collective

Status: 
Currently under intense development. 

USAGE

1. Grab the app:
git clone git://github.com/desaperados/seed.git

2. Copy config/settings.example.yml to config/settings.yml and edit accordingly

3. Generate the database: (default is sqlite3)
rake db:migrate

4. Start your server:
script/server

5. Start using seed

CURRENT FEATURES:

- Site wide embedded content creation and editing
- Override the default layout with a custom template
- Exception Notification
- Caching Mechanism

- Page Creation and Management
  - Menu Hierarchy Ordering
  - Pagination Control
  - Management of page viewing and editing rules

- Article Creation and Management  
  - Drag and drop Article Ordering
  - Integrated image upload
  - General / Video / Table style articles

- News Items Creation and Management
  - News archive 
  - Integrated image upload

- Blog Posts Creation and Management
  - News archive
  - Integrated image upload
  - Comments with Akismet spam protection 
  
- Components Creation and Management
  - Pull feeds from other pages on the site
  - Integrated document upload
  - Customise display options

- Users Module
  - Restful Authentication
  - Roles
  - Account activation via email
  - Forgotten password handling


NOTES:

Uses Lightview by Nick Stakenburg which requires a Creative Commons Licence
http://www.nickstakenburg.com/projects/lightview/
